5 senses of abandon                                                     
Sense 1
abandon
       => discard, fling, toss, toss out, toss away, chuck out, cast aside, dispose, throw out, cast out, throw away, cast away, put away
Sense 2
abandon, give up
Sense 3
abandon, give up
Sense 4
vacate, empty, abandon
       => leave, go forth, go away
Sense 5
abandon, forsake, desolate, desert
       => leave

       => succeed, win, come through, bring home the bacon, deliver the goods
Sense 2
peg
       => pierce, thrust
Sense 3
peg, peg down
       => attach
          Also See-> peg down#2
Sense 4
peg
       => stabilize, stabilise

Sense 1
settle, settle down
       => put, set, place, pose, position, lay
Sense 2
decide, settle, resolve, adjudicate
       => end, terminate
Sense 3
settle, square off, square up, determine
       => conclude, resolve
Sense 4
settle, locate
Sense 5
reconcile, patch up, make up, conciliate, settle
       => agree, hold, concur, concord
Sense 6
sink, settle, go down, go under
       => descend, fall, go down, come down
Sense 7
settle, root, take root, steady down, settle down
       => stabilize, stabilise
Sense 8
settle
       => become, go, get
Sense 9
settle
       => build up, develop
Sense 10
settle
       => stop, halt
Sense 11
settle
       => change
Sense 12
settle
       => arrange, set up
Sense 13
settle
       => accept, consent, go for
Sense 14
settle
       => agree, hold, concur, concord
Sense 15
settle
       => arrange, fix up
Sense 16
settle
       => sink
Sense 17
subside, settle
       => sink, settle, go down, go under
Sense 18
ensconce, settle
       => put, set, place, pose, position, lay
Sense 19
settle, get back
       => contend, fight, struggle
Sense 20
finalize, finalise, settle, nail down
       => end, terminate
          Also See-> settle on#1
Sense 21
settle
Sense 22
fall, descend, settle
       => come

Synonyms/Hypernyms (Ordered by Estimated Frequency) of verb shake
9 senses of shake                                                       
Sense 1
shake, agitate
       => move
Sense 2
shake, didder
       => move involuntarily, move reflexively
Sense 3
judder, shake
       => vibrate
Sense 4
rock, sway, shake
       => move back and forth
Sense 5
shake
       => weaken
Sense 6
stimulate, shake, shake up, excite, stir
       => arouse, elicit, enkindle, kindle, evoke, fire, raise, provoke
Sense 7
shake, shake off, throw off, escape from
       => escape, get away, break loose
Sense 8
shake
       => change, alter, modify
Sense 9
shake
       => gesticulate, gesture, motion

       => change by reversal, turn, reverse

       => agree, hold, concur, concord

contract, undertake
       => promise, assure
Sense 2
sign, contract, sign on, sign up
       => hire, engage, employ
Sense 3
compress, constrict, squeeze, compact, contract, press
       => tighten
Sense 4
shrink, contract
       => decrease, diminish, lessen, fall
Sense 5
contract, take, get
       => sicken, come down
Sense 6
contract
       => shrink, reduce
Sense 7
condense, concentrate, contract
       => change, alter, modify
Sense 8
narrow, contract
       => change
Sense 9
abridge, foreshorten, abbreviate, shorten, cut, contract, reduce
       => decrease, lessen, minify

       => search, seek, look for

       => check

       => change, alter, modify

13 senses of yield                                                      
Sense 1
yield, give, afford
       => supply, provide, render, furnish
Sense 2
give way, yield
       => change

       => produce, make, create
Sense 4

       => give
Sense 5
yield, relent, soften
Sense 6
move over, give way, give, ease up, yield
       => move

give, yield
       => make, create
Sense 8
concede, yield, grant
       => agree, hold, concur, concord
Sense 9
succumb, yield
       => die, decease, perish, go, exit, pass away, expire, pass, kick the bucket, cash in one's chips, buy the farm, conk, give-up the ghost, drop dead, pop off, choke, croak, snuff it

yield, pay, bear
       => gain, take in, clear, make, earn, realize, realise, pull in, bring in
Sense 11
give, yield
       => stretch
Sense 12
yield
Sense 13
yield, give in, succumb, knuckle under, buckle under
       => accept, consent, go for
